15 f. mundum: heavens, in con- trast with mare, terras. —horisz seasons. Cf. Epist. 2, 3, 302 snb verni temporis horam.

17. unde: equivalent to ex quo, referring to parens. Cf. Verg. A. 1, 6 genus unde Latinum. This use of unde, referring to a person, is chiefly found in poetry, cf. 2, 12, 7 unde = α quibus, but occurs also in prose, eg. Cic. de Or. 1, 67 ille ipse, unde cognovit.
